    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT, CONNECTING
        RODS AND PISTONS - Connecting Rods, Pistons and Piston Rings - Check Piston Ring End Clearance in Cylinder Bore
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Check Piston Ring End Clearance in Cylinder Bore</title>
        <figure id="f1200730" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1372.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking the Piston Ring End Clearance in the Cylinder Bore</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler Gauge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a piston head without piston rings installed to push the piston ring into the cylinder
                bore. Make sure the piston ring is square to the cylinder wall.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a feeler gauge to measure the gap between the ends of each piston ring. If the gap does
                not meet the specification, select another piston ring or check the cylinder bore wear again.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
